#. [part]
#: Bad_Moon_Rising/scenarios/05_Payback.cfg:15
msgid ""
"Scarrion lost conciousness.  When he awoke, he was in the lit chamber and "
"dressed in blue robes.  He jumped to his feet and noticed he felt... "
"different.  A tall, terrifying, winged woman in guilded armour was watching "
"him.  When she saw him register her presence, she gave a wolfish smile and "
"began to speak:"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Bad_Moon_Rising/scenarios/05_Payback.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Your intrusion was fortunate, we've learned much from you.  It seems we have "
"been asleep for far too long, your people have gotten quite arrogant and are "
"engaged in activities they do not understand.  They will ruin the world, we "
"must stop them.  How would you like to serve revenge to... Muordante and...  "
"Bersohn?  You will leave this mountain, rally more of your kind, and raise "
"our sleeping kindred in the depths of a cavern to the west.  From there, you "
"will assist us in saving the world from those who would destroy it.  You and "
"the faithful will bear witness to the Restoration of Order!"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Bad_Moon_Rising/scenarios/05_Payback.cfg:21
msgid ""
"And with that she turned and disappeared.  She already knew his answer:  He "
"couldn't wait to destroy the evil necromancer Muordante and the callous "
"General Bersohn.  His feet seemed to know where to go, and before he knew "
"it, he was back at Muordante's stronghold..."
msgstr ""

